 @anastasiawhite7482  well if you restrict yourself to that, then of course that would be understandable. But that wasn’t my point. Neither was gender. In fact it’s geared more toward equality among humans in general.

Im not necessarily saying AI simply taking jobs as in companies unethically replacing us. But rather freeing us from what we deem to be “life”. Life isn’t about waking up to go work for someone else.. who works for someone else… who works for many people - who work for the CEO of whatever company. But when you really think about it, all we do is waste our lives doing things for others so we can live to die, while dying to live. It’s depressing when you realize it makes no sense.

So if we had AI to replace most jobs in an ethical way that benefits everyone, you can do what you want without worrying about the things you need, just to hopefully get what you want. But my point doesn’t necessarily include AI being self sufficient on its own but because we programmed it to be. By collectively brining it to fruition. Idk I feel like I’m all over the place trying to convey this lol so if I misinterpreted anything or didn’t explain it clearly, let me know and I don’t mind revising this. And sorry for typing a lot btw.

 @schwajj  that’s the thing though. Many people are looking at it from that perspective which is understandable. But given that seems to be what everyone agrees with and limits their thoughts to, thats what makes me believe it would be a good thing rather than bad. Because companies won’t just go around replacing us and expect nothing to come from it. Cuz we wouldn’t allow it.

Im mainly speaking about a gradual progression where AI replaces basically the dumb and pointless jobs, makes the more important jobs easier, and allows more people to live the way they like, within reason. Idk I feel like most want to make it a bad thing as if it’ll takeover. Rather than it being an extension that opens up new possibilities.

Idk I like thinking if challenging ideas so hopefully it doesn’t come off as if I’m oblivious to the problematic concerns. But it doesn’t hurt to think beyond the box ppl seem to confine themselves to.
